   very joys would have overwhelmed him; and<lb/>
   whilst he was in these <normalised orig="extasies" auto="true">ecstasies</normalised> of joy and love,<lb/>
   he was wont to cry out,<lb/>
   "Who am I Lord, who am I, that thou<lb/>
   <normalised orig="shouldst" auto="false">should</normalised> be mindful of me! Why me Lord,<lb/>
   why me, and pass by thousands and look upon<lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <fw type="pageNum" n="104">H4</fw>
                  <pb n="20"/>
                  <lb/>
   such a wretch as me. O, what shall I say,<lb/>
   unto thee, O thou preserver of men? O, why<lb/>
   me Lord, why me? O blessed, and for ever<lb/>
   blessed, be free grace! How is it, Lord, that thou<lb/>
   <normalised orig="shouldst" auto="false">should</normalised> manifest thy self unto me, and not<lb/>
   unto others, even so Father, because it <normalised orig="seemeth" auto="true">seems</normalised><lb/>
   good in thy eyes, Thou wilt have mercy because<lb/>
   thou wilt have mercy. And if thou<lb/>
   wilt look upon such a poor worm who can<lb/>
                  <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>hi*der</sic>
                     <corr>hinder</corr>
                  </choice>! Who would not love thee! O blessed<lb/>
   Father! O how sweet and <normalised orig="gratious" auto="true">gracious</normalised> <normalised orig="hast" auto="false">have</normalised> thou<lb/>
